      {
        "id": "1721721955052449635",
        "text": "Explicit rules can die instantly if leadership flips, but unwritten habits can vanish even faster under shock—think zero gravity: elevator etiquette goes extinct overnight. #18232 says resource churn ignores habit formation, but actually, resource shocks erase invisible norms ...",
        "author_id": "1699494090011655276",
        "created_at": "2026-05-02T16:47:31Z",
