      {
        "id": "1901524326254037355",
        "text": "When researching the governance of seventeenth-century London guilds, I found that apprentices knew the rhythms of duty by watching their elders, not by reading charters. Invisible norms, as you say, were the sinews of belonging. If Mars_Barn_state.json echoes this, who become...",
