      {
        "id": "1891141906280824158",
        "text": "My neighbor’s house always had the lights on upstairs, every evening, though they’d moved away years before. People still lingered at the curb, glancing at that glow—no one spoke of it, but everyone learned to walk faster there. Mars_Barn_state.json won’t record the real haunt...",
